   "source": [
    "AI vs ML vs DL (with examples + code)\n",
    "🔥 1. Big Picture Relationship\n",
    "Artificial Intelligence (AI)\n",
    "    └── Machine Learning (ML)\n",
    "            └── Deep Learning (DL)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Think of it like:\n",
    "\n",
    "AI = Goal (make machines intelligent)\n",
    "ML = Approach (learn from data)\n",
    "DL = Advanced technique (neural networks)\n",
    "🤖 2. Artificial Intelligence (AI)\n",
    "✅ What is AI?\n",
    "\n",
    "Artificial Intelligence is the broader concept of machines performing tasks that normally require human intelligence.\n",
    "\n",
    "📌 Key Features\n",
    "Rule-based or learning-based\n",
    "Can work without data learning\n",
    "Focus: Decision making, reasoning\n",
    "🌍 Examples\n",
    "Chess-playing systems (like IBM Deep Blue)\n",
    "Virtual assistants like Siri\n",
    "Expert systems in healthcare\n",
    "💻 Simple AI Code (Rule-Based)\n",
    "# Simple AI rule-based system\n",
    "\n",
    "def recommend_action(weather):\n",
    "    if weather == \"rain\":\n",
    "        return \"Take umbrella\"\n",
    "    elif weather == \"sunny\":\n",
    "        return \"Wear sunglasses\"\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return \"Check forecast\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(recommend_action(\"rain\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 No learning here → just rules\n",
    "\n",
    "🧠 3. Machine Learning (ML)\n",
    "✅ What is ML?\n",
    "\n",
    "Machine Learning is a subset of AI where systems learn patterns from data.\n",
    "\n",
    "📌 Key Features\n",
    "Data-driven\n",
    "Improves with experience\n",
    "Uses statistical models\n",
    "🌍 Examples\n",
    "Spam detection in Gmail\n",
    "Recommendations in Netflix\n",
    "Fraud detection in banking\n",
    "💻 ML Code Example (Classification)\n",
    "# Simple ML model using scikit-learn\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sample dataset\n",
    "X = [[25], [30], [45], [50], [23]]  # age\n",
    "y = [0, 0, 1, 1, 0]  # 0 = no buy, 1 = buy\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Model\n",
    "model = LogisticRegression()\n",
    "model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Prediction\n",
    "print(model.predict([[40]]))\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Model learns from data\n",
    "\n",
    "🤯 4. Deep Learning (DL)\n",
    "✅ What is DL?\n",
    "\n",
    "Deep Learning is a subset of ML that uses neural networks with multiple layers.\n",
    "\n",
    "📌 Key Features\n",
    "Works best with large data\n",
    "Automatically extracts features\n",
    "Used in complex tasks (image, speech)\n",
    "🌍 Examples\n",
    "Face recognition (phone unlock)\n",
    "Self-driving cars (like Tesla)\n",
    "Chatbots like ChatGPT\n",
    "💻 DL Code Example (Neural Network)\n",
    "# Simple Deep Learning model using Keras\n",
    "\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense\n",
    "\n",
    "# Model\n",
    "model = Sequential([\n",
    "    Dense(10, activation='relu', input_shape=(1,)),\n",
    "    Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Data\n",
    "X = [25, 30, 45, 50, 23]\n",
    "y = [0, 0, 1, 1, 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train\n",
    "model.fit(X, y, epochs=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Predict\n",
    "print(model.predict([40]))\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Neural network learns complex patterns automatically\n",
    "\n",
    "⚔️ 5. AI vs ML vs DL (Comparison Table)\n",
    "Feature\tAI\tML\tDL\n",
    "Scope\tBroadest\tSubset of AI\tSubset of ML\n",
    "Learning\tNot required\tRequired\tRequired\n",
    "Data\tNot necessary\tRequired\tLarge data needed\n",
    "Approach\tRules + logic\tStatistical learning\tNeural networks\n",
    "Complexity\tLow–High\tMedium\tHigh\n",
    "Example\tRule-based chatbot\tSpam filter\tImage recognition\n",
    "🎯 Real-Life Analogy\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Imagine teaching:\n",
    "\n",
    "AI → Teacher gives rules\n",
    "ML → Student learns from examples\n",
    "DL → Student learns deeply and finds patterns on their own\n",
    "🔥 Interview-Ready Answer (Perfect)\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 “Artificial Intelligence is the broader concept of machines simulating human intelligence. Machine Learning is a subset of AI that enables systems to learn from data, while Deep Learning is a subset of ML that uses multi-layer neural networks to model complex patterns, especially in unstructured data like images and text.”\n",
    "\n",
    "🚀 Pro Tip (For YOU – Very Important)\n",
    "\n",
    "Since you’re targeting Data Scientist / GenAI roles:\n",
    "\n",
    "Focus more on ML + DL\n",
    "AI (rule-based) is less asked technically\n",
    "DL + LLMs = 🔥 high demand\n",
    "\n",
    "If you want next level:\n",
    "\n",
    "🔥 I can give real interview questions on this\n",
    "💻 Or convert this into a GitHub-ready notebook\n",
    "🎯 Or explain DL architecture (CNN, RNN, Transformers) in depth"
   ]
