   "source": [
    "The terms AI, ML, and DL are often used interchangeably, but they’re actually nested concepts—each one is a subset of the previous. Let’s break them down clearly, with examples and code.\n",
    "\n",
    "🧠 1. Artificial Intelligence (AI)\n",
    "\n",
    "In Artificial Intelligence, the goal is to create systems that can simulate human intelligence—like reasoning, decision-making, or problem-solving.\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 What it includes:\n",
    "Rule-based systems (if-else logic)\n",
    "Search algorithms\n",
    "Expert systems\n",
    "Machine Learning (subset)\n",
    "🔹 Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "A chess-playing program:\n",
    "\n",
    "Evaluates board positions\n",
    "Chooses the best move\n",
    "\n",
    "Classic AI example: Deep Blue defeating Garry Kasparov.\n",
    "\n",
    "💻 Simple AI Code (Rule-based system)\n",
    "def chatbot(user_input):\n",
    "    if \"hello\" in user_input.lower():\n",
    "        return \"Hi there!\"\n",
    "    elif \"bye\" in user_input.lower():\n",
    "        return \"Goodbye!\"\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return \"I don't understand.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(chatbot(\"hello\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 This is AI, but not ML, because it doesn’t learn—it just follows rules.\n",
    "\n",
    "🤖 2. Machine Learning (ML)\n",
    "\n",
    "Machine Learning is a subset of AI where systems learn from data instead of being explicitly programmed.\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Types:\n",
    "Supervised Learning (labeled data)\n",
    "Unsupervised Learning (patterns)\n",
    "Reinforcement Learning (rewards)\n",
    "🔹 Example:\n",
    "\n",
    "Spam email detection:\n",
    "\n",
    "Input: Emails labeled as spam/not spam\n",
    "Output: Model predicts new emails\n",
    "💻 ML Example (using scikit-learn)\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "# Features: [hours studied]\n",
    "X = [[1], [2], [3], [4], [5]]\n",
    "# Labels: pass(1) or fail(0)\n",
    "y = [0, 0, 1, 1, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "model = LogisticRegression()\n",
    "model.fit(X, y)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(model.predict([[2.5]]))  # Predict pass/fail\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 Here the system learns from data.\n",
    "\n",
    "🧬 3. Deep Learning (DL)\n",
    "\n",
    "Deep Learning is a subset of ML that uses neural networks with many layers.\n",
    "\n",
    "Inspired by the human brain.\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Key concept:\n",
    "\n",
    "Artificial Neural Network\n",
    "\n",
    "🔹 Example:\n",
    "Image recognition (detect cats vs dogs)\n",
    "Voice assistants\n",
    "Self-driving cars\n",
    "💻 DL Example (using TensorFlow / Keras)\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.models import Sequential\n",
    "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Dense\n",
    "\n",
    "# Simple neural network\n",
    "model = Sequential([\n",
    "    Dense(10, activation='relu', input_shape=(1,)),\n",
    "    Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Training data\n",
    "X = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "y = [0, 0, 1, 1, 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "model.fit(X, y, epochs=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(model.predict([2.5]))\n",
    "\n",
    "👉 This model automatically learns patterns using layers.\n",
    "\n",
    "🔁 Relationship (Important!)\n",
    "Artificial Intelligence (AI)\n",
    "    └── Machine Learning (ML)\n",
    "            └── Deep Learning (DL)\n",
    "⚖️ Key Differences\n",
    "Feature\tAI\tML\tDL\n",
    "Scope\tBroad\tSubset of AI\tSubset of ML\n",
    "Learning\tMay or may not learn\tLearns from data\tLearns using neural networks\n",
    "Data needed\tLow to high\tModerate\tVery high\n",
    "Complexity\tLow → High\tMedium\tHigh\n",
    "Examples\tChess AI\tSpam filter\tFace recognition\n",
    "🧠 Real-world Analogy\n",
    "AI → Teaching a child rules to solve math\n",
    "ML → Child learns from examples\n",
    "DL → Child learns on their own using deep thinking patterns\n",
    "🚀 When to Use What?\n",
    "Use AI (rule-based) → simple logic systems\n",
    "Use ML → structured data, predictions\n",
    "Use DL → images, speech, large complex data\n",
    "\n",
    "If you want, I can give:\n",
    "\n",
    "Real-world project ideas (resume-ready)\n",
    "Interview questions on AI/ML/DL\n",
    "A roadmap to learn these step-by-step"
